## Notes

- Phase 1 tests: `cargo test {filter}` in engine/
- Phase 2 tests: `cargo check --target wasm32` + `wasm-pack build` + artifact verification
- Phase 3-4 tests: `npx vitest run {filter}` in frontend/ — all hit real WASM engine
- No mocks anywhere. Phase 3 Stage P3-3 wires real WASM before any components are built.
- Phase 5 (Platform Layer): Auth, routing, env config, navigation, boot verification. The app must render and be navigable before polish.
- CSS bundle size check in Phase 6: `npm run build` must produce CSS > 20KB
- **Phase 7 is a HARD GATE**: Product does not ship until P7-1 (stub scan), P7-2 (completeness audit), and P7-3 (build verification) all pass. The runner's stub_scan() function mechanically blocks convergence if stubs are detected in source files at any stage.
